<h4 id="toc12"><span>My nickname is AlanDaris, I'm 19 years old. My house is in Kyiv, Ukraine, where all the apartment buildings are, and I am not married. I study Germanic philology in a university, and I get home every day by 7 PM at the latest. I don't smoke, but I occasionally drink. I'm in bed by 3 AM, and almost never make sure I get eight hours of sleep. After browsing the web on my phone for about an hour before going to bed, I usually have some problems sleeping until morning. Unlike a baby, I wake up with plenty of fatigue and stress in the morning. I was told there were plenty of issues during my last check-up. I'm trying to explain that I'm a person who does not wish to live a very quiet life. I take care to trouble myself with enemies and things like winning and losing, which sometimes causes me to lose sleep at night. That is how I deal with society, and I know that is what brings me happiness.</span></h4>
